newsitem.title: ARGENTINA: Argentine cash soybeans up after Chicago.
newsitem.headline: Argentine cash soybeans up after Chicago.

text.p: Argentine cash new corp soybeans firmed in tight trade at the Buenos Aires Cereals Exchange, with bids helped by a firmer CBOT, traders said.

Another bullish factor was the realization that Wednesday's rains did not much help soybean areas in Santa Fe and Cordoba provinces. April maize firmed in low volume trade, bids finding support in higher international prices. January wheat rose, in a technical bounce off seller's resistance. March sunflower seed firmed in tight trade. Prices were helped by firmer soybeans and oil prices.
